THAT THE CONFERENCE BE HELD FOR A PERIOD OF TWO WEEKS, PREFERABLY AT ROME, WHICH
                    WE CONSIDER THE MOST APPROPRIATE SITE FOR A U.N. CONFERENCE ON THE SUBJECT OF
                    FOOD AND AGRICULTURE;

A. DETERMINATION OF LONG-TERM WORLD FOOD AND NUTRITION REQUIREMENTS;
                    DETERMINATION OF LONG-TERM PRODUCTION REQUIREMENTS; DETERMINATION OF LIKELY
                    YEARLY FLUCTUATION IN PRODUCTION AND THE LEVEL OF STOCKS DESIRABLE TO AVOID
                    CRITICAL FOOD SHORTAGES IN A PREDICTABLE SERIES OF BAD PRODUCTION YEARS;

C. THE NATURE OF MUTUAL RESPONSIBILITIES FOR STOCKHOLDING INCLUDING THE
                    RESPONSIBILITIES OF EXPORTERS, IMPORTERS, DEVELOPED COUNTRIES, DEVELOPING
                    COUNTRIES, CENTRALLY PLANNED AND FREE MARKET ECONOMIES;
